The department says it is unable to predict the outcomes of Saturday&#8217;s meeting with unions, but they can confirm there will be no services. JOHANNESBURG The Home Affairs Department has urged the public not to visit their offices on Saturday as they will be closed.This is a result of ongoing discussions and negotiations between the department and labour unions.Spokesperson David Hlabane says the outcome of the negotiations will determine if offices will be functional next weekend.He says the department appeals to the union leadership to assist in resolving matters speedily in the spirit of the settlement agreement. It s hard to say what will happen beyond tomorrow, but we can confirm that we appeal to members of the public not visit the offices. 